shire, England, United Kingdom":"Ewyas Harold, Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1254–":"1254–Deceased","1252–Male":"1252–Deceased","1254–Male":"1254–Deceased","1256–1293":"1256–1293","1280–1318":"1280–1318","1290–Male":"1290–Deceased","1292–Male":"1292–Deceased","1260–Female":"1260–Deceased","1278–Male":"1278–Deceased","1280–1352":"1280–1352","1226–1293":"1226–1293","1236–Female":"1236–Deceased","1352":"1352","1252":"1252","1260":"1260","1293":"1293","1292":"1292","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1226":"1226","1236":"1236","1278":"1278","1256":"1256","1254":"1254","about 1278":"about 1278","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England":"Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England","Abbey Dore, Herefordshire, England":"Abbey Dore, Herefordshire, England","Ewyas Harold, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ewyas Harold, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Scudamore","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Skidmore  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Skidmore","meanings":["English (Staffordshire): of Norman origin, a variant of <b>Scudamore</b>, which most probably arises from a Norman French nickname for a knight who used a particular type of leather shield, from the unrecorded Norman French phrase, <i>escu de more</i> ‘Moor's shield’, a reference to a type of Moorish leather shield called an <i>adarga</i>, which was in widespread use not only in medieval Iberia and north Africa but also in Brittany.","History: The manor of Upton Scudamore in Wiltshire was held by Peter de Skydemore in 1216. The same manor was held by Godfrey Escudamore shortly after 1150. The Scudamore family claim descent from Ralph, recorded in Domesday Book (1086) as holder of <i>Opeton</i> (Upton), whose son was known as Reginald <i>Escudemor</i>."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":5,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":36,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":61,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":74,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Scudamore Lord Kentchurch was born in 1254, in Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England, his father, Peter Scudamore - Lord of Upton Scuda